HEADWORD: Brand goose
<hw>Brand" goose`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <ety>[Prob. fr. 1st
<ets>brand</ets> + <ets>goose</ets>: cf. Sw. <ets>brandg⟦aring⟧s</ets>.
Cf. <er>Brant</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A species of wild
goose (<spn>Branta bernicla</spn>) usually called in America
<altname>brant</altname>. See <er>Brant</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

